{
  "text": "Of the clinical variables recorded in this study, few had significant predictive power to identify patients likely to have a PKD2 mutation. In the multivariate model adjusting for gender and hypertension, point estimates suggested that non-PKD2 disease, male gender and the presence of hypertension may together be associated with earlier onset of CKD3 (Additional file 2: Table S2 ), although formal significance levels were not reached in this cohort due to its size. However, the directional nature of the effect supports previous reports indicating a milder renal phenotype with PKD2 mutations [CITATION_1] .",
